   <note>This document is a letter dated June 4, 1837 from George Lewis Welcker to his brother Henry Inman Welcker in Talladega, Alabama. George writes of his recent relocation to Terre Haute, Indiana and describes his pleasant trip and all the old friends he met on the way. He briefly discusses his military duties in Terre Haute, inquires about the family, and discourages his brother from venturing into a business partnership in Talladega.</note>
